args: Lathna was truly terrified of the Nyarlathotep\nwithin her, but Curran and Heinwald's strong\nbelief helps to restore her confidence.
Welp, she ran off. What now, Heinwald?
Leave her. We have little to gain\nfrom pursuing her at this juncture.
Yeah, I suppose we have more\npressing matters in front of us.
Our name is Chaos. Our name is Nil.\nOur name is Nyarlathotep!
Awake at last. Goodness, but you certainly\nmade that quite the ordeal.
Hey, nothing wrong with sleeping in now\nand then. Anyways, let's get a move on.
N-no, I can't. I'm not me.\nI'm...Nyarlathotep.
Yeah, it sure seems like it. ...So?
You must use your words carefully, Lathna.\nYou being Nyarlathotep and you NOT being\nyourself are, in fact, very different things.

If I might borrow the words of the one from
the archives, Nyarlathotep as a name is
not bound by a single sobriquet or form.
Instead, it is a being of many faces.
＂Nyarlathotep＂ refers to multitudinous\nentities all existing in concert.
And while it strains credulity, I believe it\npossible that you are one of the multitude.
However, that in itself does not constitute\nproof that you are not, in fact, YOU.
In short, you are most certainly Lathna,\nand there is no reason for us to avoid\nor otherwise be rid of you.
But what if I turn into Nyarlathotep and\ndo something terrible to you without\neven realizing it?
And when have you ever done\nsomething terrible?
Just because I haven't done anything bad\ndoesn't mean it will stay that way.
It's true that no one knows if a person\nwill commit an evil act in the future.
But we're all the same in that regard.\nANYONE could do something bad.
Listen, Lathna. The timing of when you\nchange is very clearly up to you.

You do it when you want to keep people
away from you, or when you're in danger.
And you don't change when it makes you
feel bad.
What I'm saying is, YOU are in control\nof the Nyarlathotep within you.
Do you see? So long as you're yourself,\neven if you ARE Nyarlathotep, there is\nnothing to worry about.
Who you MIGHT be isn't important.\nHeck, no one really knows who they\nactually are, anyway!
So instead of trying so hard to figure out\nwho you are, you ought to think about\nwho you WANT to be.
That will give you something to hold on to\nso that you can remain yourself.
You didn't mess up what you said.
Heh. I'm going to let you in on a juicy little\nsecret, Lathna—Curran doesn't actually\nhave a problem being articulate.

It's only when he tries to act cool that he
ends up mangling his words. If he tries to
do something that doesn't suit him, for
example, no good will come from it.

That means he wasn't just telling you
what he thought you wanted to hear.
Instead, he was speaking honestly,
from his heart.
Dammit, Heinwald! Now that you've\nspilled the beans, the magic is gone!
Heh... Hee! Hee hee hee hee!
THERE'S a smile! Sheesh,\nit took you long enough.
Most problems in life can be solved by\njust keeping a good, healthy attitude.\nYou should always remember that.
If the going gets tough or you feel yourself\nstarting to worry, just try to be positive.
Goodness, you came all the way here\njust for little old me? What a thrill.
But what possible need could you have\nof a pathetic woman whose desires\nhave been brought to heel?
I was wondering if you hadn't actually\nachieved your objective after all.

The cruelest of questions, coming as it
does from the man responsible for
crushing said objective. Why on earth
would you ever wonder such a thing?
You had Teinsom in the palm of your hand.\nYou had countless chances to outwit us.
The fact you never did so tells me the\nsituation was never out of your control.
You came all the way here to confirm that?
What can I say? I have a vested interest\nin learning where your true motives lie.
Then perhaps you might think on this:\nWhat is the goal of the cock who crows\nlong before the coming of the dawn?
No. You have but half of it.
The drowsing, faceless fragment\nstill remains here, yes?

But no matter. Let us, instead, turn to the
little matter of YOU. I find you interesting
indeed, sir. Perhaps you might watch the
coming of the new dawn with me?
Before we share in the twilight,\nI have another question.
